The paper deals with the problem of computing the Sparse Fourier Transform (sparse FFT) with a block sparse model, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory (cs.IT, cs.SP). The paper also uses adaptivity to achieve improved sample complexity, which is a common technique in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve geometric and combinatorial ideas, which are often studied in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm on real-world datasets, which is a common theme in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
